If this part is malfunctioning, you may not be able to open or close your door. In some instances, it may seem like your door is closing, but if it is not latching properly you won’t be able to start your drying cycle. You should replace this part as soon as it’s malfunctioning. Your dryer may run even though the latch is malfunctioning, but it is unsafe if the dryer continues to run while the door is open. This replacement part features 1 door latch kit which includes 2 strikes, 3 catches, and a set of instructions. This model is constructed of plastic and metal, and comes in white/silver.

name: Sump Drain Hose 00645149
description: This genuine OEM drain hose is designed to facilitate proper wastewater removal from select dishwashers and refrigerators. It connects the appliance’s sump to the household drain system, ensuring efficient drainage and preventing water accumulation. Constructed for durability and reliability, this hose helps maintain optimal appliance performance. Common signs of failure include slow draining, residual water in the tub, or pooling around the unit. Installation requires turning off both the power and water supply, and following the appliance’s manual for model-specific instructions. For safety, gloves and protective gear are recommended during installation.
installation_steps: Disconnect power and shut off water supply.
Access the hose connections and place a towel to catch drips.
Loosen clamps, swap the hose, and tighten securely.
Restore water and run a quick cycle to check for leaks.

name: SPRAY ARM 00668385
description: This upper spray arm assembly is a genuine OEM component designed to distribute water throughout the upper rack of the dishwasher during wash cycles. It rotates to ensure even coverage, helping to remove food residue and improve overall cleaning performance. Engineered for durability and precision, this part is compatible with select dishwasher models and serves as a direct replacement for worn or malfunctioning spray arms. Installation involves securing the arm to its mounting point, ensuring proper alignment for optimal rotation and water flow. Replacing a damaged spray arm can restore cleaning efficiency and prevent uneven results.
installation_steps: Open the dishwasher and pull out the rack for room.
Twist or unclip the old spray arm/support and lift it off.
Seat the new part and ensure it spins freely.
Run a rinse cycle to confirm smooth rotation.

name: Damper Control Assembly 242303001
description: This authentic OEM damper control assembly is designed to be compatible with refrigerators. The assembly regulates the airflow between the freezer and refrigerator compartments. When the refrigerator needs to cool down, the damper receives signals from the thermostat or control board to open and allows more cold air from the freezer to enter the refrigerator compartment. When the desired temperature is reached, the damper closes to restrict airflow. If the damper assembly is faulty or damaged, your fridge will be unable to maintain the desired temperature levels. It may be either too warm leading to food spoilage or too cold leading to frost buildup.
